# Postgres parameterized type normalization

- When using `format_type`, only rely on it for parameterized types (strings with parentheses); keep base native types otherwise.
- Normalize Postgres synonyms: `varchar` → `character varying`, `bpchar` → `character`, `varbit` → `bit varying`.
- Normalize time zone aliases: `timestamp ... with time zone` → `timestamptz`, `time ... with time zone` → `timetz`, strip `without time zone`.
- Schema verification should accept base native types when `typeParams` are present but the schema omits parameters.
